article_title: Death Toll Rises to 5 in School Shooting
article_text:
SEATTLE — A fifth teenager has died as a result of a Washington State high school shooting two weeks ago that began when a student opened fire in the cafeteria.

The victim, Andrew Fryberg, 15, died of his wounds Friday evening, Harborview Medical Center in Seattle said.

Zoe Galasso, 14, was killed during the shooting Oct. 24, by a freshman at Marysville-Pilchuck High School.

Gia Soriano, 14, died Oct. 26 at Providence Regional Medical Center in Everett, and another 14-year-old, Shaylee Chuckulnaskit, died Oct. 31 at the Everett hospital.

Advertisement Continue reading the main story

The attacker, Jaylen Fryberg, 14, died of a self-inflicted gunshot wound.

Andrew was the last wounded student still hospitalized.

On Thursday, another student who was shot during the episode, Nate Hatch, 14, was released from Harborview. He had been shot in the jaw.

More than 200 friends and relatives gathered along the road leading onto the Tulalip Indian Reservation north of Seattle to welcome Nate home. He was driven past the crowd in a tribal police vehicle.

Andrew and Nate were cousins of the killer.
